                            <comment id="12905868" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 3 Sep 2010 12:13:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see a big thread-safety problem here, as there should be no functional effect even if two getEncodingManager() calls happened to end up creating parallel EncodingManager instances.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I agree that using static singleton instances is a better approach here, so I did that in revision 992271. Note that this rendered the getEncodingManager() method unnecessary, so I decided to simply remove it instead of keeping it around as a deprecated method. It was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-601&quot; title=&quot;PDFBox performance issue:  PDSimpleFont, PDFont performance tweaks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-601&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-601&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and should probably never have been non-private to start with.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
